<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Grey1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Grey,</orth> name 1) of Sir Thomas G., a conspirator under Henry V: <bibl n="shak. h5 2.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 58</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 58</bibl> 2) the first husband of Edward the Fourth's queen: <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.3.174" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.127" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 127</bibl>. 3) his and Queen Elizabeth's son, Lord G.: R3 <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">1, 3</bibl>, <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">1, 3</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.66" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 66</bibl> etc.
